01:11.418 --> 01:13.409
Hot meat, senor.

01:15.055 --> 01:18.422
[ Sportscaster ] He knocked the
goal-tender down. Can you believe that?

01:18.492 --> 01:21.359
[ Sportscast Continues
In Background ]

01:58.965 --> 02:00.933
[ Radio Static ]

02:05.839 --> 02:08.899
[ Garbled Radio Transmission ]

02:11.645 --> 02:13.806
Hey, amigo.

02:13.847 --> 02:16.179
[ American Accent ]
Que paso esta noche?

02:18.084 --> 02:20.450
How's the roast beef?.

02:20.520 --> 02:23.751
Uh,   Como esta el carne?

02:25.659 --> 02:28.423
Bueno...

02:30.530 --> 02:33.693
...o malo?

02:35.001 --> 02:38.528
[ Crewmen Cheering ]

02:52.252 --> 02:54.550
Come on!

02:57.123 --> 03:00.684
Where's our illustrious
communications offiicer?

03:14.641 --> 03:16.836
Hey, Ed.
What gives with the--

03:20.146 --> 03:22.546
What the hell are you doing?!

03:25.752 --> 03:28.482
That's enough!

03:31.625 --> 03:34.492
Ed.

03:37.030 --> 03:38.998
Oh, man.

03:46.907 --> 03:49.000
Now you've gone
and done it.

04:01.688 --> 04:04.054
Dejame!

04:04.090 --> 04:06.081
Dejame!

04:07.260 --> 04:09.285
No, no, no.

04:09.529 --> 04:11.554
No, no, no, no!

04:11.631 --> 04:13.622
[ Screaming ]

05:28.875 --> 05:30.934
Am I interrupting
anything, Agent Mulder?

05:32.979 --> 05:35.641
Nothing you'd be too terribly
interested in, Agent Doggett.

05:35.715 --> 05:38.741
[ Drops Keys On Table ]

05:38.818 --> 05:42.720
Agent Mulder, what are
you doing down here?

05:42.789 --> 05:45.189
I'm looking into the recent
death of an oil worker.

05:45.258 --> 05:48.421
Yeah, I got a heads-up on it
from you a couple of days ago.

05:48.662 --> 05:50.653
That's what I'm doing here.

05:50.730 --> 05:55.030
Agent Mulder, I understand that you had
more than just a proprietary interest...

05:55.101 --> 05:57.069
in these cases,
but I can't help it...

05:57.137 --> 06:00.868
if you're not assigned
to this unit anymore.

06:00.940 --> 06:05.707
I didn't see any reason
to pursue this oil worker case.

06:05.779 --> 06:08.304
Well, maybe you missed the fact
that this victim's corpse...

06:08.381 --> 06:10.906
washed ashore
at PortAransas, Texas.

06:10.984 --> 06:13.714
Massive flash burns
on 90 percent of his body.

06:13.787 --> 06:16.984
I read the report, Agent Mulder,
if you're insinuating I didn't.

06:17.057 --> 06:19.355
Then you must also know that
this man was not the only man...

06:19.392 --> 06:22.987
to disappear from the Galpex-Orpheus
platform that night, but one of two men.

06:23.063 --> 06:25.122
The communications offiicer
is also missing.

06:25.198 --> 06:29.225
The company attributes that to an
explosion on the rig-- a ""blowout''--

06:29.302 --> 06:32.738
which is what they say caused
Simon de la Cruz's burns.

06:32.806 --> 06:36.173
Burns the M.E. said in his
report were not inconsistent...

06:36.242 --> 06:38.233
to exposure
to high levels of radiation.

06:38.311 --> 06:42.008
""Not inconsistent.'' That's not exactly
what I'd call a ringing endorsement.

06:42.082 --> 06:45.108
These fiiles include the same
kind of radiation phenomena.

06:45.185 --> 06:48.484
- Tissue destroyed by exposure to--
- Black oil.

06:50.957 --> 06:54.859
Five years ago you and Agent Scully
investigated a case of
a World War II plane...

06:54.928 --> 06:57.453
salvaged from the bottom
of the Pacifiic Ocean...

06:57.497 --> 06:59.431
where a substance was
brought to the surface...

06:59.499 --> 07:01.433
which you describe as
a highly contagious virus...

07:01.501 --> 07:05.369
of extraterrestrial origin that
has radioactive properties...

07:05.438 --> 07:08.965
and can take over a man's body
and is part of an alien conspiracy...

07:09.008 --> 07:11.476
to colonize the planet,
if I'm not mistaken.

07:11.711 --> 07:14.339
And you'd love to help, but you
left your light saber at home.

07:16.750 --> 07:18.911
How'd you get stuck
down here, Agent Doggett?

07:20.453 --> 07:24.253
Kersh catch you peeing
in his corn flakes?

07:24.324 --> 07:26.258
[ Phone Rings ]

07:36.469 --> 07:38.403
John Doggett.

07:38.471 --> 07:41.406
[ Scully ] The Deputy Director
is waiting, Agent Doggett.

07:41.441 --> 07:43.466
Yeah, I was just
on my way up.

07:43.543 --> 07:47.980
Why didn't you tell me that you were
pursuing this Texas oil worker case?

07:48.047 --> 07:51.847
- Because I'm not.
- Well, there's an exec here
from the oil company...

07:51.918 --> 07:54.910
who says that he was contacted
by a man in our offiice.

07:56.456 --> 07:58.424
No, that'd be Agent Mulder.

08:00.226 --> 08:02.023
What are you talking about?

08:02.095 --> 08:04.996
I'm going to let him
answer that.

08:09.769 --> 08:11.760
Just like old times.

08:14.073 --> 08:16.564
Now it's all making sense.

08:19.579 --> 08:21.979
Tough crowd.

08:27.086 --> 08:29.054
Mr. Ortega...

08:29.122 --> 08:32.523
this is
Special Agent Fox Mulder...

08:32.592 --> 08:35.288
the person you spoke to
on the phone, I believe.

08:35.361 --> 08:38.261
Mr. Ortega is Vice President
of Operations...

08:38.331 --> 08:41.857
for Galpex Petroleum
out of Galveston, Texas.

08:41.934 --> 08:43.903
I believe
we did speak, yeah.

08:43.937 --> 08:47.134
[ Kersh ] There's also confusion
about who spoke to certain...

08:47.207 --> 08:49.368
government offiicials
who seem to think...

08:49.409 --> 08:52.503
the FBI is running
an investigation into the accident.

08:52.579 --> 08:55.309
That would've been me
as well, sir...

08:55.381 --> 08:58.817
and that was in the best interests
of the FBI and Mr. Ortega, I believe.

08:58.885 --> 09:01.319
[ Kersh ]
Mr. Ortega would beg to differ.

09:01.387 --> 09:03.912
As would I.

09:03.990 --> 09:08.051
[ Ortega ] You've complicated an already
sensitive situation, Agent Mulder.

09:08.127 --> 09:11.528
Galpex Petroleum has discovered
what we think may be...

09:11.598 --> 09:15.329
a massive new oil province
beneath the Gulf of Mexico--

09:15.401 --> 09:17.198
one that would give
a huge advantage...

09:17.270 --> 09:20.933
fiinancially and politically
to whoever gets to drill it.

09:22.976 --> 09:28.107
- Who else are we talking about?
- U.S. territorial waters cover
the northern half of the Gulf.

09:28.181 --> 09:30.149
Our wells are on our side...

09:30.216 --> 09:32.912
but the fiield may spread
well to the south.

09:32.986 --> 09:35.454
The government of Mexico
could claim it's theirs.

09:35.521 --> 09:38.490
This incident has nothing
to do with that whatsoever.

09:38.524 --> 09:42.119
It's about the unexplained
death of Simon de la Cruz.

09:42.195 --> 09:44.322
Simon de la Cruz
was a Mexican national...

09:44.364 --> 09:46.389
killed in a U.S.
business enterprise.

09:46.466 --> 09:49.196
They'd like nothing better
than to use his death...

09:49.269 --> 09:51.237
to get us to abandon
the Orpheus rig...

09:51.304 --> 09:54.000
so they can be the fiirst
to drill the province.

09:54.040 --> 09:57.373
Leaving me no choice now but to
conduct a criminal investigation...

09:57.410 --> 10:00.140
quickly and quietly to take away
any legal position...

10:00.213 --> 10:02.147
that would affect
American interests.

10:02.215 --> 10:04.308
A criminal investigation is not
going to clear up anything.

10:04.384 --> 10:07.251
You've done more than enough,
Agent Mulder, thank you.

10:07.320 --> 10:10.289
I don't think you know exactly what
you're dealing with here, sir.

10:10.356 --> 10:14.122
- No, I think I do, Agent.
- This is an X-File.

10:14.193 --> 10:17.253
And I'm sending someone
from the X-Files to investigate.

10:17.330 --> 10:21.061
You're talking about an oil rig
that's 150 miles out at sea.

10:21.100 --> 10:25.537
- You can't send a pregnant woman.
- I'm not sending Agent Scully.

11:12.018 --> 11:15.317
Yuri Volkoff, your new
communications specialist.

11:15.388 --> 11:18.016
- You bring your new gear?
- Yes, it's in there.

11:18.057 --> 11:20.992
-John Doggett, Special Agent.
- Who?

11:21.060 --> 11:24.188
- From the Bureau.
- FBI, you say?

11:24.263 --> 11:26.731
Yeah. Someone told you
I was coming, I hope.

11:26.966 --> 11:29.764
No, just the new
comm equipment.

11:29.969 --> 11:32.233
You got radio problems?

11:32.305 --> 11:34.273
No one told you
about me coming?

11:34.307 --> 11:36.639
We still got ship-to-shore.

11:36.709 --> 11:39.610
But when they gave us the message,
it said just one agent was coming.

11:39.679 --> 11:42.671
Right.
I'm the one agent.

11:42.749 --> 11:45.479
Well, then, who's the guy
that got here this morning?

11:45.551 --> 11:49.043
The one in talking with
our crew chief right now?

12:00.800 --> 12:03.166
Agent Mulder.

12:03.236 --> 12:06.501
- Can I have a word with you?
- Will you give me a minute?

12:06.539 --> 12:09.133
I'm just getting fiilled in on
the details of this investigation.

12:09.208 --> 12:11.233
Why don't you pull up a seat
and introduce yourself...

12:11.310 --> 12:13.801
and Mr. Taylor won't
have to repeat himself.

12:20.053 --> 12:21.816
Bo Taylor.

12:22.055 --> 12:24.546
I was on deck watch the night
this thing went down.

12:33.232 --> 12:35.700
Go on, Mr. Taylor.

12:35.768 --> 12:40.228
Men can go off
the deep end out here.

12:40.306 --> 12:43.298
It's like
a cabin fever of sorts.

12:43.376 --> 12:46.777
They're hundreds of miles away
from their family and their friends...

12:46.846 --> 12:48.609
six weeks at a stretch.

12:48.681 --> 12:52.310
Some of them might just
as well be doing hard time.

12:52.385 --> 12:56.481
So how's that fiigure with
the victim, Simon de la Cruz?

12:56.556 --> 13:01.323
Well, mestizos are usually
the most reliable men I know...

13:01.394 --> 13:03.830
on the drill floor.

13:03.830 --> 13:04.819
on the drill floor.

13:05.098 --> 13:08.295
But Simon just
lost his nut, I guess.

13:08.334 --> 13:11.497
It's the only good explanation.

13:11.571 --> 13:13.698
Simon de la Cruz's body
was found with flash burns.

13:13.773 --> 13:16.241
What's that got to do with him
going off the deep end?

13:16.309 --> 13:19.506
Well, hell, he tried
to blow the whole damn rig.

13:19.579 --> 13:24.141
I mean, it was sabotage
pure and simple.

13:24.217 --> 13:27.744
He knocked the cock off a gas valve
and he must've sparked it...

13:27.820 --> 13:30.653
because it went faster
than a Friday paycheck.

13:30.723 --> 13:35.160
- What about the second victim?
- Communications chief, wasn't he?

13:35.228 --> 13:39.164
Probably never knew
what hit him.

13:39.232 --> 13:43.100
What's the communications chief
doing on the drilling floor?

13:43.169 --> 13:48.129
A man can die out here, sir,
just going for a walk.

13:48.207 --> 13:51.404
Probably what happened
when it blew.

13:51.477 --> 13:54.241
Nobody even knew
he was gone...

13:54.313 --> 13:56.304
till the shift change.

13:56.382 --> 14:00.751
Well, I guess that's it--
in a nutshell.

14:00.786 --> 14:02.754
Thank you, Mr. Taylor.

14:05.224 --> 14:07.556
Agent Mulder.

14:19.939 --> 14:21.873
[ Doggett ]
Agent Mulder!

14:21.941 --> 14:24.273
Don't walk away when
I'm talking to you.

14:24.343 --> 14:26.436
Like it or not, I've
been assigned this case.

14:26.512 --> 14:29.777
One call to the Deputy Director and
you're canned for insubordination.

14:29.849 --> 14:32.147
How're you going to call
when the radio's broken?

14:32.218 --> 14:34.186
Hey, don't push me,
Agent Mulder.

14:34.220 --> 14:37.781
- You won't do it.
- You think?

14:37.857 --> 14:39.791
We're both in the same
boat, Agent Doggett...

14:39.859 --> 14:41.793
we're just paddling
in different directions.

14:41.861 --> 14:43.795
No, we're not going in
different directions here.

14:43.863 --> 14:45.763
We're going in one
direction: my direction.

14:48.868 --> 14:52.599
I don't think Kersh expects you to come
back empty-handed on this one.

14:52.672 --> 14:56.199
And since you've already told me
what you think about this case
in so many words...

14:56.275 --> 14:58.334
I don't see you coming
back with anything...

14:58.411 --> 15:00.436
that's going to protect
anybody's business interests...

15:00.513 --> 15:02.413
let alone your own ass.

15:02.481 --> 15:05.177
Wow, you really got me pegged.

15:05.251 --> 15:07.515
Anything that doesn't fiit
in my narrow fiield of vision...

15:07.587 --> 15:09.851
might as well not exist,
is that right, Agent Mulder?

15:11.824 --> 15:15.885
So why is this man Taylor lying?
You do know he's lying?

15:15.962 --> 15:19.227
I think he knows the truth
about what happened.

15:19.298 --> 15:22.665
And he may not be the only one.

15:22.735 --> 15:26.569
I never would've believed it,
these stories about you.

15:26.639 --> 15:28.869
Really?
What stories are those?

15:28.941 --> 15:32.240
That you could fiind a conspiracy
at a church picnic.

15:33.246 --> 15:35.009
What church?

15:56.869 --> 15:59.531
- Agent Scully?
- Close the door and lock it.

15:59.605 --> 16:02.870
- You said you wanted
to see me right away.
- I didn't know who to talk to...

16:02.908 --> 16:05.900
- and I haven't been able
to reach Agent Mulder.
- About what?

16:05.978 --> 16:10.881
About what I found in my autopsy
of the oil rig accident victim
Simon de la Cruz.

16:10.916 --> 16:12.884
Agent Scully, this man's body
was supposed to be...

16:12.918 --> 16:15.386
transported back to Mexico
completely intact.

16:15.421 --> 16:19.585
I found it by accident in
the third ventricle of his brain.

16:24.964 --> 16:27.364
- Agent Scully--
- No, it's okay, it's all right.

16:27.433 --> 16:29.560
What do you mean? I was
under the impression this stuff...

16:29.635 --> 16:31.603
could literally jump
into a man's body.

16:31.637 --> 16:34.697
No, it can, and I've seen that
happen, but that's the thing.

16:34.774 --> 16:37.709
I mean, this man was clearly
infected by the alien virus.

16:37.777 --> 16:41.042
It entered his system and it
was massing in the pineal gland.

16:41.280 --> 16:43.441
But it's dead.

16:44.383 --> 16:46.317
What killed it?

16:46.385 --> 16:48.785
Well, intuitively, you would say
the same thing that killed him:

16:48.854 --> 16:50.822
exposure to high
levels of radiation.

16:50.856 --> 16:55.316
But it makes no sense because the
virus itself has radioactive properties.

16:55.394 --> 16:57.328
Somebody needs to tell
Agent Doggett that.

16:57.396 --> 16:59.557
He needs to have an idea
of what he's dealing with.

16:59.632 --> 17:03.398
No, you need to tell Deputy
Director Kersh that he has to order...

17:03.469 --> 17:06.461
a controlled evacuation
of that rig, right now.

17:06.539 --> 17:08.507
Don't ask me to go to
Kersh with this evidence...

17:08.540 --> 17:11.009
telling him to order an evacuation
for something you can't even explain.

17:11.077 --> 17:14.911
If the virus is loose,
Agent Doggett's life is in danger.

17:14.980 --> 17:17.813
We don't know that for sure.

17:17.883 --> 17:23.685
There are nearly two dozen men on
that rig and not one other case. Why?

17:31.464 --> 17:33.432
[ High-pitched Static ]

17:49.115 --> 17:51.106
Hey, Yuri.

17:51.150 --> 17:54.984
Heard you had some
problems with the radio.

17:55.054 --> 17:58.080
New gear's all on-line,
working fiine.

17:58.157 --> 18:01.456
Only there's some sort of
high-frequency interference...

18:01.527 --> 18:03.757
that I have no idea
how to get rid of.

18:03.829 --> 18:06.559
Hear that?

18:06.632 --> 18:11.126
That's a signal that's
coming in and fiiltering in...

18:11.370 --> 18:14.430
across a large range
of channels.

18:14.507 --> 18:17.567
You know, I don't think I have any
choice but to power down and restart.

18:17.643 --> 18:19.577
No.

18:19.645 --> 18:21.772
You can't do that.

18:23.916 --> 18:25.941
I hate to argue with you.

18:55.080 --> 18:57.742
[Woman ] This is the Marine
Operator for Galpex-Orpheus.

18:57.817 --> 18:59.785
Come in, Orpheus.

19:03.989 --> 19:07.015
Galpex-Orpheus,
I have a priority transmission.

19:07.092 --> 19:10.755
Repeat, this is
a priority transmission.

19:13.833 --> 19:15.926
This is Orpheus, go ahead.

19:16.001 --> 19:18.902
Orpheus?

19:18.971 --> 19:20.962
I've been trying
to reach you for hours.

19:21.040 --> 19:22.974
This is Special Agent
Dana Scully.

19:23.042 --> 19:26.637
I have an urgent message for
an investigative agent on board...

19:26.712 --> 19:28.680
an agent John Doggett.

19:28.747 --> 19:31.238
I'm ready
to take that message.

19:31.484 --> 19:35.113
No, I'm sorry. I need to speak
with Agent Doggett directly.

19:38.023 --> 19:40.924
I got it.

19:40.993 --> 19:43.757
I'm sorry,
Agent Doggett's gone fiishing.

19:43.829 --> 19:45.854
Can I take a message, please?

19:45.931 --> 19:48.161
Mulder?

19:48.234 --> 19:50.168
I was just in the neighborhood.

19:50.236 --> 19:53.000
Mulder, you can't just
flout orders like this.

19:53.072 --> 19:56.064
It's not like old times.
Kersh isn't going to tolerate this.

19:56.141 --> 19:58.769
- Kersh doesn't need to know.
- Mulder--

19:58.811 --> 20:02.144
You need me out here, Scully.
You know that better than anyone.

20:02.181 --> 20:05.150
Well, I hate to say as of
this morning, I'd have to agree.

20:05.217 --> 20:08.880
Who's flouting orders?
You found something, didn't you,
in that victim's body?

20:08.954 --> 20:11.946
- The virus?
- Yes, I did...

20:12.024 --> 20:14.618
- and it's dead, Mulder.
- Dead?

20:14.693 --> 20:16.786
- What killed it?
- Possibly radiation.

20:16.862 --> 20:18.796
No, that's not possible--

20:18.864 --> 20:21.697
I know, I know, and this
could be an isolated event...

20:21.767 --> 20:25.294
but that he's infected at all means that
everybody out there could be at risk...

20:25.538 --> 20:28.063
and that means
you and Agent Doggett.

20:28.140 --> 20:30.108
We've got
to quarantine this rig.

20:30.175 --> 20:32.575
No, Mulder, you need
to get off the rig.

20:32.645 --> 20:34.613
Have Agent Doggett
give the order.

20:34.680 --> 20:38.047
We can quarantine you and
the crew when you get back here.

20:38.117 --> 20:40.551
Scully, if these men are infected,
the last place we want them...

20:40.586 --> 20:42.554
is on shore where
they can infect other people.

20:42.588 --> 20:44.886
You're sitting on the answer
right there, Scully.

20:44.924 --> 20:48.951
The body--you fiind the virus,
you can fiind what knocks it out,
you can fiind what kills it.

20:49.028 --> 20:51.758
And what if I can't?

20:51.830 --> 20:54.060
Well...

20:54.133 --> 20:57.591
when he, uh, gets old enough, you
tell the kid I went down swinging.

20:57.670 --> 21:00.969
Let me talk
to Agent Doggett.

21:01.040 --> 21:03.031
Agent Doggett's
not here right now.

21:03.108 --> 21:06.305
Yes, I am.
Who's on the radio?

21:09.815 --> 21:11.783
Who are you talking to?

21:11.817 --> 21:14.115
- Hey!
- That was Agent Scully.

21:14.153 --> 21:16.621
- What'd she say?
- She said it was lucky
that I'm out here.

21:16.655 --> 21:18.646
No, you're lucky
I'm letting you stay.

21:20.192 --> 21:23.286
If you've got important
information, I better know about it.

21:23.329 --> 21:25.297
I'm in charge out here,
Agent Mulder.

21:25.331 --> 21:27.356
All right, then go ahead
and take charge.

21:27.600 --> 21:29.795
Only you might not like
what it means in this case.

21:29.868 --> 21:33.702
What you're going to have
to do with that information
you're so anxious to have.

21:38.043 --> 21:41.308
All right, listen up!
I'll make this brief.

21:41.380 --> 21:43.575
We've been given an order
to quarantine the rig.

21:43.649 --> 21:45.583
[ Startled Murmuring ]

21:45.651 --> 21:48.848
As of 1400 hours, we're offiicially
shut down and locked down.

21:48.887 --> 21:50.855
We're going to be
stuck here a while.

21:50.889 --> 21:52.857
All flights in and out
have been suspended.

21:52.891 --> 21:54.882
- [ Men Shouting And Muttering ]
- I know, I know.

21:54.960 --> 21:59.021
We've been asked to cooperate until the
FBI is certain everything's shipshape.

21:59.098 --> 22:01.066
Now, for everybody's
protection...

22:01.100 --> 22:03.227
we need to all of us
cooperate fully.

22:03.268 --> 22:06.260
- Oh, man!
- Protection from what?

22:06.305 --> 22:08.637
From a possible contagion.

22:09.908 --> 22:11.842
- Anybody here feel sick?
- No!

22:11.910 --> 22:13.844
All right, all right,
knock it off!.

22:13.912 --> 22:16.779
I need everybody to check
their water consumption.

22:16.815 --> 22:20.114
- And we'll be cutting back
to half-rations.
- [ Men Murmuring ]

22:25.391 --> 22:27.689
I've been going over
the crew manifest, Mr. Saksa...

22:27.760 --> 22:30.160
- and there seems to be a problem.
- Problem with what?

22:30.229 --> 22:33.027
According to the manifest, there's
supposed to be 18 men on board.

22:33.098 --> 22:35.032
I count only 17,
including you.

22:35.100 --> 22:37.193
This is my whole crew in here.

22:38.303 --> 22:43.172
Um, Diego Garza.
Where's he?

22:43.242 --> 22:45.904
- Who?
- A deckhand.

22:45.978 --> 22:50.074
Friend of Simon de la Cruz, the
man who tried to sabotage the rig.

22:56.355 --> 22:59.688
- Well, I'll be damned.
- What, he's not here?

22:59.758 --> 23:02.659
Any idea where
he might be?

23:02.728 --> 23:06.755
Well, he didn't leave the rig.
Not by any means I know of.

23:06.832 --> 23:08.857
What do you say
we go fiind him?

23:11.303 --> 23:14.204
[ Scully ] This man
was exposed to a virus.

23:14.239 --> 23:18.198
And... why do I
need to see this?

23:18.277 --> 23:21.337
To understand what your crew
may be infected with--

23:21.413 --> 23:24.211
what they risk spreading
on or off that rig.

23:24.283 --> 23:27.013
You understand Galpex
is eager to cooperate.

23:27.086 --> 23:29.054
But shutting down
a producing rig...

23:29.121 --> 23:32.955
costs in the neighborhood
of $150,000 a day.

23:32.991 --> 23:36.688
And according to my OIM,
no one on that rig is sick.

23:36.762 --> 23:38.957
They're just
hungry and tired.

23:38.997 --> 23:40.965
You don't know that for sure.

23:40.999 --> 23:44.093
What symptoms would they be
showing? What would we see?

23:44.169 --> 23:48.970
Unexplained behavior.
Possible detection in the eyes.

23:49.007 --> 23:52.170
- We've seen none of that.
- You're relying on suspect data.

23:52.244 --> 23:54.269
I'm relying on medical reports.

23:54.346 --> 23:56.837
And unless you
give me more than this...

23:56.882 --> 23:58.941
I'm calling that
Orpheus crew back in.

23:59.017 --> 24:02.475
Bringing them home and rotating
a fresh crew onto that rig.

24:02.721 --> 24:04.712
Oh, my God.

24:07.493 --> 24:12.192
[ Door Opens And Closes ]

24:12.264 --> 24:14.892
So what are you hoping to fiind,
Agent Mulder, honestly?

24:14.967 --> 24:16.901
I'm hoping to fiind
Diego Garza.

24:16.969 --> 24:18.903
Slim chance of that,
if you ask me.

24:18.971 --> 24:21.531
The crew boss said it-- a man
could disappear off this platform...

24:21.774 --> 24:23.742
and no one
would even notice.

24:23.776 --> 24:26.802
Did you see that the crew manifest
listed Diego Garza as mestizo--

24:26.879 --> 24:30.747
- of mixed Mexican descent--
just like his friend who died?
- Yeah, so what?

24:30.783 --> 24:34.014
Well, the crew chief said these
mestizo were particularly good workers.

24:34.086 --> 24:36.213
Now we've got one dead
trying to sabotage the rig...

24:36.288 --> 24:38.256
and another one who's missing.

24:38.290 --> 24:41.885
One of their best workers--you'd
think somebody'd notice him missing.

24:41.960 --> 24:44.224
Yeah, so,
maybe he's still here.

24:44.296 --> 24:47.754
Maybe he's just waiting to fiinish
the job that killed his friend...

24:47.800 --> 24:50.098
to protect Mexican
oil interests.

24:50.135 --> 24:52.968
These men are hiding something,
but that's not it.

24:55.140 --> 24:57.404
You know, I quarantine
a whole damn oil rig...

24:57.476 --> 25:01.537
without any evidence to support
what you're saying-- not one damn thing.

25:01.780 --> 25:03.805
But you still have yet
to give me a straight answer...

25:03.882 --> 25:05.941
as to what you think
is going on out here.

25:06.018 --> 25:08.043
Now, if these men
are hiding something...

25:08.120 --> 25:10.816
if they're protecting something,
then what the hell is it?

25:10.889 --> 25:14.450
- I don't know yet.
- Well, when you do, let me know...

25:14.526 --> 25:17.984
'cause I've got to get on
the radio to justify this action.

25:24.536 --> 25:28.905
Agent Doggett, I didn't come
out here just to bust your ass.

25:28.974 --> 25:31.875
I'm telling you,
I've seen this substance.

25:31.944 --> 25:34.003
I've seen how it can
take over a man's body.

25:34.079 --> 25:36.070
This crew could be infected
and not even know it.

25:36.148 --> 25:39.515
They may have no idea
they're being controlled.

25:42.354 --> 25:44.288
This?

25:44.356 --> 25:47.814
This is what you're saying
is going to take over my body?

25:49.228 --> 25:51.321
Well, when's it
going to kick in?

25:51.396 --> 25:54.160
That's not how it works.

25:54.233 --> 25:56.098
It body jumps
from man to man.

25:56.168 --> 25:58.102
And I'm not sure
that it's in all oil.

25:58.170 --> 26:03.130
Well, that's a relief,
because only 90% of the planet
is dependent on the stuff.

26:05.978 --> 26:08.310
The man from Galpex Oil lied.

26:08.380 --> 26:10.473
What?
He's infected, too?

26:10.549 --> 26:13.575
No, that new oil province
that he wants to protect--
it's already in production.

26:13.652 --> 26:16.917
It's being pumped and drilled
by this rig. That's how
this crew got infected.

26:16.989 --> 26:19.480
You're reaching,
Agent Mulder.

26:19.558 --> 26:24.120
Billions and billions of barrels
lying right underneath us,
waiting to be produced.

26:24.196 --> 26:26.960
Waiting to infect that 90%
of the planet you talked about.

26:27.032 --> 26:30.934
These men are hiding something?
That'd be something to hide.

26:31.003 --> 26:32.937
But, Agent Doggett...

26:33.005 --> 26:35.974
what if that's why this man
is in hiding-- Diego Garza--

26:36.041 --> 26:38.509
because he knows what they're up
to and he knows what they're up to...

26:38.543 --> 26:41.376
because he's the only one who's not
infected with this alien virus?

26:41.446 --> 26:45.109
All right, he knows. Then why doesn't
he just come down and tell us?

26:45.183 --> 26:48.914
[ Emergency Buzzer ]

26:59.932 --> 27:01.957
It's the radio room!

27:08.307 --> 27:10.400
I'll fiind another one.

27:39.972 --> 27:42.065
Agent Scully.

27:44.109 --> 27:47.203
- Sir.
- You're in a hurry.

27:47.279 --> 27:49.713
To do what?

27:49.948 --> 27:53.008
To continue
with my work, sir.

27:53.085 --> 27:57.715
I'm not privy
to this... ""work.''

27:57.956 --> 27:59.719
I thought this body...

27:59.958 --> 28:02.586
would've been well on its way
back to Mexico.

28:02.661 --> 28:05.027
[ Door Opens ]

28:08.600 --> 28:12.969
I obviously haven't been able
to rely on those...

28:13.038 --> 28:17.304
whose job it is to keep me
apprised and informed.

28:17.376 --> 28:21.176
I have to rely
on phone calls.

28:21.246 --> 28:24.545
Like the call I received
from Martin Ortega.

28:24.616 --> 28:29.144
Why doesn't somebody
make me privy...

28:29.221 --> 28:33.214
to who the hell gave the order
to shut down that rig?

28:36.094 --> 28:38.585
I did.

28:38.663 --> 28:42.759
Well, I'm giving the order
this quarantine is lifted.

28:43.001 --> 28:47.438
We could do that, sir, but all
radio contact's been cut off.

28:47.506 --> 28:49.440
As soon as
it's reestablished...

28:49.508 --> 28:51.476
I want that rig
up and running...

28:51.510 --> 28:53.671
and the entire crew
choppered off...

28:53.745 --> 28:56.077
the Galpex-Orpheus
and debriefed.

28:56.148 --> 28:58.207
Sir, I think
that's a mistake.

28:58.283 --> 29:01.650
I think it'd be a mistake
not to, Agent Scully.

29:03.021 --> 29:06.184
And you're running out
of mistakes--

29:06.258 --> 29:10.194
both you
and the Assistant Director.

29:19.404 --> 29:22.305
If I didn't know better...

29:22.374 --> 29:25.138
I'd say this
was a Mulder stunt.

29:50.602 --> 29:52.797
This stuff
was all brand-new.

29:52.871 --> 29:56.329
What is it about this room
that inspires men to violence?

29:56.408 --> 29:58.342
You think this fiire
was set?

30:02.214 --> 30:05.741
- Molotov cocktail, anyone?
- [ Sniffs ]

30:05.817 --> 30:08.308
Can I borrow your radio,
Mr. Saksa?

30:08.353 --> 30:10.344
Agent Doggett, you there?

30:10.422 --> 30:13.152
Agent Doggett?

30:13.191 --> 30:16.388
Pick up, Agent Doggett.
You copy?

30:18.096 --> 30:20.087
[ Groans Softly ]

30:21.900 --> 30:24.130
Agent Doggett?

30:28.406 --> 30:30.397
Come in, Agent Doggett.

30:30.442 --> 30:32.410
Where the hell are you?

30:40.886 --> 30:43.548
[ Speaking Spanish ]

30:43.588 --> 30:45.351
Yeah, my blood's red!

30:55.834 --> 30:59.600
Tranquilo. I don't
speak very good Spanish.

31:03.508 --> 31:05.772
Diego?

31:07.179 --> 31:10.148
Tu eres Diego Garza?

31:17.222 --> 31:20.521
You're going too fast.
Are you saying you set the fiire?

31:20.592 --> 31:22.617
What are you afraid of?

31:32.204 --> 31:34.832
- Ya vienen!
-   Vienen?

31:34.906 --> 31:37.170
Vienen. ""They're coming''?

31:37.242 --> 31:39.267
Who?

31:39.344 --> 31:41.608
Who's coming?

31:53.258 --> 31:55.453
- [ Scully ] I think I've got something.
- [ Skinner ] What?

31:55.527 --> 31:59.395
This is an SEM image pulled at
random from anonymous donors.

31:59.431 --> 32:03.458
Blood-- more specifiically,
normal T-cell antibodies.

32:03.535 --> 32:05.730
By comparison...

32:05.770 --> 32:08.432
these are from the blood
of the oil rig worker.

32:08.506 --> 32:11.532
T-cells in impossible numbers.

32:11.610 --> 32:15.944
In layman's terms, this victim
was a virus-fiighting machine.

32:15.981 --> 32:19.417
- How do you explain that?
- Well, there are isolated cultures--

32:19.484 --> 32:22.942
Northern Italy for one-- where people
are immune to certain diseases--

32:22.988 --> 32:26.719
heart disease in that case--
through a genetic mutation.

32:26.791 --> 32:31.785
So this man had what? A kind
of genetic immunity to alien virus?

32:31.863 --> 32:33.922
Well,
his employment records...

32:33.999 --> 32:38.459
list Mr. Simon de la Cruz
as of mixed Mexican ancestry...

32:38.536 --> 32:40.902
when, in fact,
he is Huecha Indian.

32:40.972 --> 32:44.373
The Huecha are an
indigenous Mexican culture...

32:44.442 --> 32:47.411
that has a rare,
undiluted gene pool.

32:47.479 --> 32:52.280
Now, these genes may have
an innate immunity to infection.

32:52.350 --> 32:54.318
Okay, so he was immune
to the virus.

32:54.386 --> 32:56.320
That's still not
what killed him.

32:56.388 --> 32:59.482
- He died from being burned.
- No, not burned--

32:59.557 --> 33:02.526
irradiated, because the virus
had no effect on him...

33:02.594 --> 33:06.325
and the crew members
who were infected by the virus
couldn't control him.

33:06.398 --> 33:08.992
So they killed him
by irradiating him.

33:09.067 --> 33:12.298
Then why not kill Mulder?
Or Agent Doggett?

33:12.370 --> 33:17.740
- Why kill only this man?
- This man must've been a threat
because of something he knew.

33:17.776 --> 33:21.439
- What?
- That I don't know.

33:25.483 --> 33:27.451
So even if we did know...

33:27.485 --> 33:30.852
and were able to
get word to them...

33:30.922 --> 33:36.622
it'd put Mulder and Agent Doggett
in danger, too, wouldn't it?

33:50.675 --> 33:52.643
Su familia?

33:52.677 --> 33:55.578
La fotografiia?
Your family?

33:57.382 --> 33:59.509
You want to get
back to them?

34:01.453 --> 34:03.478
I can help you.

34:03.555 --> 34:07.491
Senor...
Confiia en mi.

34:07.559 --> 34:10.960
Yo no confiio en nadien.

34:11.029 --> 34:13.725
Great.

34:13.797 --> 34:16.358
You trust no one.

34:22.107 --> 34:26.635
But if you stay here, they will
fiind you, just like your friend.

34:30.447 --> 34:33.576
You let me go
and we'll get you back home.

34:35.420 --> 34:37.684
You have my word.

34:38.790 --> 34:40.849
Mi promesa.

34:58.877 --> 35:01.437
[Taylor ]
Where's Garza?

35:07.886 --> 35:10.616
Where is he?

35:13.658 --> 35:15.649
I'm going to go get
Agent Mulder.

35:36.981 --> 35:40.974
Agent Doggett. There's
more where that came from.

35:46.624 --> 35:49.787
- You know anything about
radios, Agent Doggett?
- Yeah, I know a little.

35:49.861 --> 35:52.921
Well, see if what little you know can
get that ship-to-shore working.

35:52.997 --> 35:55.557
- To call who?
- Anybody who can get us
off here before--

35:55.633 --> 35:58.796
- [ Banging On Door ]
- Get to work!

35:58.870 --> 36:01.464
[ Banging Continues ]

36:16.488 --> 36:19.048
[ Banging Resumes ]

36:41.279 --> 36:43.713
- Agent Doggett!
- I'm working on it!

36:43.748 --> 36:46.080
[ Mulder ] I don't think this
door can hold much longer.

36:46.117 --> 36:48.779
[Wagner's ""Ride
of The Valkyries''Playing ]

36:48.853 --> 36:51.287
- Wagner?
- What do you want?

36:51.523 --> 36:53.991
I take it back.
It's perfect.

36:54.058 --> 36:56.049
Hold this. Hold it.

36:59.297 --> 37:01.731
[Woman ]
This is the marine operator.

37:01.799 --> 37:06.668
I repeat, this is an emergency priority
transmission for the Galpex-Orpheus.

37:06.738 --> 37:11.198
Yeah, you got John Doggett on board
the Galpex-Orpheus. Come in.

37:11.276 --> 37:14.211
- This is John Doggett.
- [ Scully ] Agent Doggett?

37:14.279 --> 37:16.213
Agent Scully, yeah,
I'm right here.

37:16.281 --> 37:18.306
- Can you hear me?
- Yes!

37:18.550 --> 37:20.916
- [ Banging ]
- What was that?

37:21.953 --> 37:24.148
That's someone
knocking on the door.

37:24.188 --> 37:26.782
Mulder, listen to me.

37:26.858 --> 37:30.316
I think I know why they killed this
man, if not how they killed him.

37:30.528 --> 37:32.996
Right now we got bigger
problems. We need a chopper.

37:33.064 --> 37:34.929
We've got choppers on the way.

37:34.999 --> 37:37.297
Tell her all the men here
are infected.

37:37.535 --> 37:41.767
She's got to get
the word to the choppers
not to land on the platform.

37:41.839 --> 37:44.899
Well, how are they
supposed to get us?

37:44.976 --> 37:48.571
Well, that issue
is rapidly becoming moot!

37:48.646 --> 37:52.605
Agent Scully, listen.
There are three men on board
here that are not infected--

37:52.684 --> 37:56.552
me, Mulder and a man named Diego
Garza, who may be mentally unstable.

37:56.588 --> 37:58.579
Could be why he tried to
wreck this radio equipment...

37:58.656 --> 38:01.022
just like his friend,
Simon de la Cruz.

38:01.092 --> 38:05.085
He may resist rescue because
he believes there men in flying
saucers are coming to get him.

38:05.163 --> 38:09.065
Agent Scully, did you get that? Agent
Scully? You're breaking up, Agent--

38:13.304 --> 38:17.206
-What the hell are you doing?
-Destroying their ability to transmit...

38:17.275 --> 38:19.641
just like Diego
and Simon de la Cruz.

38:19.711 --> 38:22.077
- What are you talking about?
- I'm talking about contact.

38:22.146 --> 38:24.774
Contact with who?
The mothership?

38:24.849 --> 38:28.148
- Agent Doggett, listen.
- Now, you just back off.

38:28.186 --> 38:30.882
No, no, no. Listen.

38:45.903 --> 38:47.871
[ Doggett ]
Where'd they go?

38:47.905 --> 38:51.170
I don't know, but I don't want
to stick around to fiind out.

38:53.344 --> 38:55.312
Let's go, Agent Doggett.

39:04.822 --> 39:07.086
Agent Mulder.

39:07.158 --> 39:09.092
We can't leave him.

39:09.160 --> 39:11.628
- Who?
- Diego Garza.

39:11.696 --> 39:14.187
Agent Doggett!

39:14.265 --> 39:16.233
Diego? Diego?

39:16.300 --> 39:18.325
Donde estas?

39:18.403 --> 39:19.927
Diego.

39:19.971 --> 39:21.962
Diego, get up.
Come on, let's go.

39:27.879 --> 39:30.643
Is he coming?

39:38.690 --> 39:40.658
No.

39:40.725 --> 39:43.353
[ Helicopter Approaching ]

39:47.231 --> 39:49.665
Galpex-Orpheus, this is
Alpha-Baker-X-Ray 46...

39:49.734 --> 39:51.668
requesting
permission to land.

39:51.736 --> 39:53.670
Come in, Galpex-Orpheus.

39:54.872 --> 39:57.170
Agent Doggett, I think
I know why they let us go.

39:57.241 --> 39:59.106
What?

39:59.177 --> 40:02.704
Agent Mulder, what are you
talking about? What's going on?

40:05.149 --> 40:06.878
- They're going to blow the rig.
- Who?

40:13.725 --> 40:15.716
Let's go.

41:19.791 --> 41:21.850
- [ Man ] Abandon ship...
- What's he saying?

41:21.926 --> 41:23.917
[ Garbled P.A. Broadcast ]

41:23.995 --> 41:25.986
I think he wants
us to jump.

41:28.800 --> 41:30.893
[ Doggett ] All right,
wait a minute, Agent Mulder.

41:30.968 --> 41:34.961
I'm in charge here.
On a two count.

41:35.039 --> 41:37.007
How about a 20 count?

41:38.009 --> 41:40.034
One... two!

41:40.111 --> 41:42.944
[Yelling ]

42:11.275 --> 42:13.539
Where's the fiire,
Agent Doggett?

42:13.611 --> 42:15.545
I've been called up to see
Deputy Director Kersh...

42:15.613 --> 42:18.081
as have Agent Scully
and A.D. Skinner.

42:18.149 --> 42:20.413
I think it's all
hitting the fan.

42:20.484 --> 42:22.315
You mean with Galpex Oil?

42:22.386 --> 42:24.217
Word came down
that Galpex...

42:24.288 --> 42:28.122
has lost the right to drill
that entire Texas oil province.

42:28.192 --> 42:30.319
That oil should stay
right where it is.

42:30.394 --> 42:34.296
You should do everything in your
power to make sure that it does.

42:34.365 --> 42:37.300
- Me?
- [ Phone Ringing ]

42:39.604 --> 42:43.631
That is the deputy director calling to
tell you there's no need to see you--

42:43.875 --> 42:46.070
that the blame has been
properly assigned...

42:46.143 --> 42:48.304
for what happened
out on that platform.

42:49.647 --> 42:52.616
I'm out.

42:52.850 --> 42:55.341
I'm eighty-sixed,
Agent Doggett.

42:56.621 --> 42:59.886
What do you mean?
You're out of the FBI?

42:59.924 --> 43:03.883
Kersh could barely contain
his happiness when he...

43:03.928 --> 43:05.919
stuck it to me.

43:05.963 --> 43:09.296
So you're taking the fall.

43:10.635 --> 43:13.934
- Not for me.
- For you, for the X-Files.

43:13.971 --> 43:16.371
You're all the credibility
this offiice has left.

43:16.440 --> 43:19.375
You have Kersh's ear
and you've seen it now.

43:19.443 --> 43:23.937
Out on that platform,
you saw it for yourself.

43:23.981 --> 43:26.279
[ Phone Ringing ]

43:26.317 --> 43:29.650
Answer the phone,
Agent Doggett.

43:29.687 --> 43:32.952
You're in charge here now.

44:27.478 --> 44:29.513
[ Child ]
I made this.

44:29.513 --> 44:31.504
[ Child ]
I made this.

